title: For Sale:  HK P30 SK LEM V1 Lite w/  Trijicon HD Orange Night Sights
location: St. Peters / Old Monroe, St. Louis, Missouri
postcontent:
FOR SALE : Heckler & Koch P30SK LEM V1 Lite (4.5 # trigger pull) with UPGRADED Trijicon HD u-notch night sights, serrated rear and, an orange front. That and all the factory goods. The firearm has seen 75 rounds of Hornady Critical Defense, cleaned and put up. 
 
So kinda how it all breaks down is by definition the gun is categorized as an enhanced DAO. However it's a bit different than most other DAO guns. When the slide is racked (loading the gun), the mainspring is compressed and kept in place as with any single action mechanism. However, the external part of the hammer moves fully forward and so does the trigger. In essence you have a cocked pistol that doesn’t look cocked. The first shot has a longer trigger movement like a traditional double action pull, but it’s not any heavier than subsequent trigger pulls. The reset is a little longer than some striker-fired guns or a 1911, but it’s only about a third of the total trigger travel arc. 
 
So because of that you get the benefits of having a "single action" trigger pull with the added benefits of a re-strike capability. That along with getting the very tried and true design of the P30 pistol line up.

title: For Sale:  Palmetto State Armory M4 .223/5.56 FN Herstal barreled upper
postcontent: Purchased August 2015 and ~ 500 rounds through it.  Just picked up a deal on a piston system build I couldn't pass up so this goes to the bench in favor of a new AR-10 in .308.  The best aspect of this PSA is the FN Herstal barreled upper. 16" Mil-spec steel barrel, A2 profile, chambered in 5.56 NATO, with a 1:7 twist, chrome lined bore and M4 barrel extension. 100% made in Columbia, SC(where PSA is based out of) by FN Manufacturing at their North American HQ.  Barrels are high pressure tested, mag particle inspected and finished off with a .750 diameter low-profile gas block, 11" PSA Keymod free float rail, Picatinny flat top and an A2 flash hider. Barrels is marked "5.56 NATO 1/7 CL MP PALMETTO".  You would be hard pressed to find a higher quality barrel than an FN at any price point in the AR/M4 world.  The lower is a PSA as well machined from aluminum forgings 7075-T6, hardcoat anodized MIL-A-8625F, Type III, Class 2, milspec diameter receiver extension, M4 stock, staked M4 lock nut, standard carbine buffer and an un-notched hammer compatible for 9mm use.  The stock has a home made cheek riser with closed cell foam on it to keep my sight picture as effortless as possible, but of course it can be taken off if it doesn't suit your setup.  I don't think that will be the case though very few people today understand rifle fit and it's link to repeatable accuracy as almost no stocks off the line are set up for the masses.   The BCG is PSA's premium and made of mil-spec carpenter 158 steel, Shot peened, high pressure tested and mag particle inspected.   Gas key is machined out of bar stock, chrome lined phosphate coated, and secured with grade 8 fasteners and staked per mil-spec. Bolt carrier is phosphated outside and chrome lined inside.  The charging handle is a PSA gunfighter which is fantastic if you decide to run a scope so you don't have any issues racking a round.  Aftermarket I added a 5" Picatinny rail on the bottom forward section of the KeyMod handguard in addition to a QD swivel and mount for 1 1/4" webbed slings.  It's been properly installed and secured with LocTite Blue thread locker.  Currently there is a standard USGI 2 point sling on it since I shoot offhand quite a bit when not in a climber, but I will include a 2 point adjustable Condor Speedy as well which attaches to the buttstock and allows a few more options when hiking around.  You will receive 3 brand new never used Magpul 30 round mags with dust covers so you are going to be ready to hit the range with everything you need to have a lot of fun.  I will also include an old school Colt alloy 8 round mag which will come in handy if you ever try to use a Lead Sled b/c the older models don't let you fit the rifle upright with a hi cap mag.  This rifle will not come sighted in as I had a Leupy 12x on it which is not for sale it's going on my AR-10.  There is a set of Magpul MBUS iron sights on as you can see though so you are fully ready to hit the range.  These came off another AR I rarely use so they are not sighted in for this PSA(I reset them to mechanical zero).  I will also throw in a spring loaded bipod which packs up small and is easy to take into the field with you on a hunt.  It's helped me take many a hog.This is a cash only sale and for pick up at my home in South Tampa please.  If you have a valid FL carry permit we can do the entire transaction at my home.  If you don't have a permit then the only way I will conduct the sale is if we have a local dealer do a NICS check and you fill out the appropriate forms.  Sorry to be a stickler, but this is my comfort zone.  I'm happy to pay the NICS and FFL fees for the transaction at a local dealer.  If you have a favorite that's fine I have a local outfit I like as well.  I prefer a small mom and pop dealer in Brandon just great folks, but we can work that out if we get that far.

title: For Sale:  Rare Browning Hi Power 9mm Low serial number
location: Burlington, Raleigh / Durham / CH, North Carolina
postcontent: Extremely rare Browning Hi-Power 9mm. There were approximately 8000 of these produced and issued. The serial number is at the beginning of the run and features the police departments code of arms with shield in front of the sight. This pistol is unique for several reasons. Firstly, limited production of 8000 and this is serial number 0XXXX. It is an all there every number matching pistol including mags and box. This is the combat model known as the pre-T model. 1961 and before, features the original combat sights and internal extractor. To my knowledge this is the only example for sale like it. One other can be found but it is a post 61 that features the tangent sights and is known as the C-series. Moving along the shield located in front of the sight is actually backwards. Normally the top of the shield is closest to the shooter and the bottom further away. However, in this example the top of the shield is actually pointing away from the shooter and the bottom of the shield is closer to the shooter. Finally, the condition of the pistol is great. All of the markings can be read and seen. Making it easily identifiable and this weapon was issued to a specialized unit within the Buenos Aires police department. They were the individuals that you didn't want to visit you at home. I have personally shot this weapon and it is without a doubt the most accurate semi-auto I have ever shot. This is an amazing and rare example of a Browning Hi-Power. Unfortunately I must sell it. If you have any questions please contact me. More pictures can be made available upon request. I have edited the picture to make the serial numbers unreadable. It can be made available for any serious inquirey.

The Zeus product line is based on the latest FLIR Tau 2 VOx microbolometer core and is composed of ten (10) different models -- each optimizing performance, price and state of the art technology for a variety of uses and mission applications ranging from the seriously committed hunter to the military designated marksman. While primarily designed as a weapon scope, the Zeus functions equally well in its collateral assignments as a magnified spotting scope or handheld thermal imager.The Zeus is a solid state, uncooled, long-wave infrared, magnified dedicated weapon scope intended for day and night engagements without the need to remove the sight from the rifle. The 24/7 mission capability is only one of the strengths of Zeus. The thermal imaging technology also allows you to detect targets by cutting through snow, dust, smoke, fog, haze, and other atmospheric obscurants. Unlike the use of laser targeting or near-infrared illumination to augment night vision equipment, the Zeus Thermal Imaging Weapon Sight is extremely difficult to detect with other devices as it emits no visible light or RF energy.In addition to being the smallest and lightest in their class, Zeus Thermal Imaging Weapon Sights are characterized by their simple and intuitive controls, functions and features that are layered among direct button adjustments, direct combination button functions, and electronic menu selections. This "layering" of easy-to-understand control functions provides the operator with a framework for customizing his preferences and exploiting the robust variety of setting options available in the Zeus. The Zeus has a series of selectable color modes based on a rich, upgradeable software package. A wireless remote switch is included to activate the Zeus Thermal Imaging Weapon Sight when positioned in the "standby" mode. The Zeus has the ability to record imagery and is equipped with a video-out capability in operator selectable NTSC or PAL formats. The Zeus uses the same multi-pin connector to provide both video-in imagery, where there is a need for map or rangefinder display overlays, and external power access.Zeus weapon installation is easy, repeatable, and reliable based on a unique and highly user-friendly MIL-STD-1913/WEAVER/PICATINNY rail compatible quick-release locking mechanism. The solid state technology and software algorithms combined with a complimentary color reticle platform used in the Zeus Thermal Imaging Weapon Sight ensure maximum reticle contrast, high level target accuracy, and boresight retention that cannot be achieved with mechanical boresight adjusters and traditional ballistic drums. This level of accuracy is translated into the electronic zoom (e-zoom) function of the Zeus Thermal Imaging Weapon Sights which can be progressively increased from 1x to 2x and 4x without changing the point-of-aim to point-of-impact relationship of the targeting reticle.Armasight is convinced that the Zeus Thermal Imaging Weapon Sight represents one of the most sophisticated sighting devices available to hunters, SWAT Teams, and the Military on the market today based on superior price-to-performance value.Special User-Adjustable Imaging ToolsActive Contrast Enhancement (ACE) -- a digital "Contrast" correction that allows for a smart scene optimization based on dynamic adjustments where a variety of contrast levels occur depending on relative scene temperature.Second Generation Digital Detail Enhancement (DDE) -- a "Sharpness" correction that is digitally enhances the picture to present clearer imagery, significantly improves edge sharpening and further reduces image noise.Smart Scene Optimization (SSO) -- a fine-tuning computational correction that significantly improves an overall visual acuity for targets that have thermal signatures similar to a surrounding background.Automatic Gain Control (AGC) -- a "Gain" correction that used to automatically adjust the gain to an appropriate range, the weaker the image signal, the stronger the gain.User-Controlled Manual Non-Uniformity Correction/Flat-Field Correction (UCMNUC/FFC). There is a mechanical shutter between the camera sensor and the lens. This shutter is used to perform a non-uniformity correction (NUC) also known as flat-field correction (FFC. During FFC, the shutter presents a uniform temperature source to each detector element in the array. While imaging the flat-field source, the camera updates the offset correction coefficients, resulting in a more uniform image after the process is complete.
